Node.Notes: Occurs only once. Related to words meaning "to be agitated/restless." Contextual guesses include "rage/be in an uproar/assemble/consult together/conspire).
Chains and fetters are figures for rule and control.
Hebrew vowel pointing indicates "to break." The LXX read different vowels onto the word, which yielded to shepherd (in the sense of to rule).
May refer to any kind of rod/shepherd's staff/ruler's scepter. Coordinate with rendering for the verb for this clause.

Node.FrameGloss: {A0:kings of;ones ruling of;Unspecified A1:son of me;Unspecified}

Node.Notes: This is the Aramaic word for "son." Hebrew word spelled this way means "clean/pure." Many change the text because they doubt it can mean "Kiss the son!" But context of psalm 2 with establishment of rule of God's son makes it probable.
